from test: 24 Diffusion across the membrane. As water is taken up by the membrane on the cathode side, it back diffuses due to concentration gradients with a time scale given bywhere the diffusivity is computed for conditions of T=70°C and λ=3 . This time scale is faster than the rate at which the membrane takes in water due to chemical reactions (time scale 3); thus, it can be expected that the distribution of water within the membrane is in quasi-steady-state during water uptake.
