from test: 25 Advection in the gas channels. Because the sensor measures only the gas concentration in the bipolar plate flow passages, the time required for gas flow from the inlet to the outlet affects the sensor response to changes in membrane water content. For the anode flow rates of 0.25slpm and a total flow passage volume of 3.15cm3 , the time scale for this advective transport is 0.76s , which is close to the order of the anode outlet water vapor dip.
